result.name: Sky 100 Hong Kong Observation Deck

reviews.text: Stunning views of Hong Kong Island, Victoria Harbour and the Kowloon Peninsula are to be seen and photographed from the Sky 100 observation tower. It is situated on the 100 floor accessed by a modern high speed lift. It is 393 metres above sea level and is the only observation deck in Hong Kong offering 360 views. It was a partly cloudy day but we still got some fantastic views and some photographs. It is well worth a visit even if you have to take the ferry.

A pure tourist attraction.  An interesting place other than the Peak to see the city from above.  The facility wasn’t that great.  Unlike similar “aerial” sighting spots in other countries that may wow you from the elevator onward, Sky100 only had the 360º  view to offer.  No thoughts were seemingly given to amaze you which made this place well below average among its peers.  Wouldn’t have come but for the free tickets.  No a bad place for tourists though.  Wouldn’t take too much of your time.

Bought the tickets through Klook which helped avoid the queue . It's cheaper as well. This place is easily reachable through Kowloon MTR / Elements Mall. I was really surprised by the fact that there is no time limit for viewing unlike other places. Most prefer to visit this place 1 hour before sunset. View would be stunning if there is no mist. There is a cafe by Ritz Carlton at the top.Do remain few minutes after the sunset to enjoy the beautiful lights and music. I would rate this as one of the best observation points for Hong Kong since it gives you pretty much a 360 degree view of the place.

Bought the tickets through Klook which helped avoid the queue . It's cheaper as well. This place is easily reachable through Kowloon MTR / Elements Mall. I was really surprised by the fact that there is no time limit for viewing unlike other places. Most prefer to visit this place 1 hour before sunset. View would be stunning if there is no mist. There is a cafe by Ritz Carlton at the top. This place is stroller friendly in case you are travelling with kids. Do remain few minutes after the sunset to enjoy the beautiful lights and music. I would rate this as one of the best observation points for Hong Kong since it gives you pretty much a 360 degree view of the place.
Love the view. You can use octopus card to get in. Around $58. Shades and hat would have helped since there's no sun roof on the top
